eins - A tool for measuring network-bandwidths and -latencies.

eins is not sockping!

Copyright (C) 2006  Hynek Schlawack <hs+eins@ox.cx>

Based on `sockping' by Lars Schneidenbach <lschneid@cs.uni.potsdam.de>.

Parameters:

Client:
  All:
    -i numtries: Number of measures. Default is 54.

  Mods:
    -t t: TCP
       u: UDP
       b: BMI

  Options:

    TCP & UDP:
      -6: Use IPv6
      -h header-size: Prepend with a header
      -p port: Portnumber to use. Default is 8910.